article_metadata.description: Gov. John Kasich’s expansion of Medicaid through Obamacare provided health-care coverage to about 640,000 poor Ohioans. Now, an estimated 130,000 people stand to lose that coverage through the legislature’s misguided “Healthy Ohio Program.” This program, if approved by federal regulators, would require many beneficiaries to pay into a modified health savings account.
